      info vurl "http://developer.berlios.de/project/showfiles.php?group_id=1824"
      info good 20120905
      info last 20110831
      info home http://fetchmail.berlios.de/
      info docs http://fetchmail.berlios.de/fetchmail-man.html
      desc 'retrieves remotely stored email
fetchmail is a remote mail retrieval and forwarding
utility intended to be used over on-demand TCP/IP
links (such as SLIP or PPP connections).
It supports every remote-mail protocol now in
use on the Internet: POP2, POP3, RPOP, APOP,
KPOP, all flavors of IMAP, ETRN, and ODMR.
It can even support IPv6 and IPSEC.'
